# ============================================
# Text Control Codes ($F0-$FF)
# These control text display, not characters
# ============================================
# F0=[WAIT]      - Wait for button press
# F1=[ITEM]      - Insert item name
# F2=[SPELL]     - Insert spell name
# F3=[NAME]      - Insert character name
# F4=[MONSTER]   - Insert monster name
# F5=[NUMBER]    - Insert number
# F6=[CTRL-F6]   - Unknown control
# F7=[CTRL-F7]   - Unknown control
# F8=[CTRL-F8]   - Unknown control
# F9=[CTRL-F9]   - Unknown control
# FA=[CTRL-FA]   - Unknown control
# FB=[CTRL-FB]   - Unknown control
# FC=[CTRL-FC]   - Unknown control
# FD=[LINE]      - Line break / clear line
# FE=[CTRL-FE]   - Scene/window control
# FF=[END]       - String terminator

# ============================================
# 2-Byte Control Code
# ============================================
# $22 XX = Position/formatting control
#   The XX byte is a parameter (seen: 03, 04, 07, 09)
#   Example: 22 07 = [POS:7] before "The Royal Soldiers"

# ============================================
# Notes on Byte $40
# ============================================
# $40 appears to be a string terminator in some contexts
# (item/spell name tables in Bank 18)
